deck: Outpouring Comics started as a couple of friends role playing a super powered universe and has evolved into a small press publisher of comics over time.  Their goal is to make you enjoy every turn of the page craving more. Happy Reading!
description:
Outpouring Comics started as a couple of friends Role Playing together and creating stories while in college. These stories evolved and two of the Role Players eventually went on to start their own universes, characters, and stories. Both creators brought in a small group to assist in creation and expansion of their universes before bringing any comic to readers eyes. In June 2012 the two universes merged together to bring about the creation of Outpouring Comics.

Outpouring Comics made their first public appearance debut at Asbury Park Comic Con in April 2014 with the comic VODA #1

In July 2015 Outpouring inked exclusive deals with comic veterans Rusty Gilligan (Recollection Magazine, Mac and Trouble) and John Orlando (Journey into Madness, Cybergen, Doc Behemoth, The Intruder, FHA-Q) for all current and future comics, graphic novels, and other products associated with their comic book properties.

Outpouring Comics publishes the ongoing series VODA, Vampire of the Lost Highway, The Guardian, Brigg's Empire, and Manifest Destiny to name a few. Outpouring separates their lines into two different branches. One is a collaborative universe they call the Outpouring Universe (VODA, Briggs Empire, Manifest Destiny). The other is called Outpouring Network and consists of creator owned titles being published by Outpouring (Vampire of the Lost Highway, The Guardian, Journey into Madness, Cybergen, Mac and Trouble).

Outpouring Comics has made it their goal to have their readers enjoy every turn of the page.
name: Outpouring Comics

description:
Imprint of Macmillan Publishing.

Picador launched in 1995 and has grown into one of the larger imprints for literary fiction and nonfiction in the United States. Picador is the literary trade paperback imprint for Macmillan. They publish paperbacks from Farrar Straus & Giroux, Henry Holt & Co. and St. Martin's Press.

Picador has, among other successful authors, signed Pulitzer Prize winners like Michael Chabon, Michael Cunningham, Jeffrey Eugenides, Thomas L. Friedman, Tony Horwitz and Marilynne Robinson.

description:
Curio & Co. understands collecting and collectors. Each of us can recall that first childhood treasure – a smashed penny, a toy from the bottom of the cereal box, a rubber band with “You’re the bestest” written on it by Jenny McKenzie – and we remember feeling “this is so special that I have to keep it forever.” So we did.

We know that memories have powers so strong they can take you back to a specific time and place in your life that you can live over and over again. And sharing those memories with others can be just as powerful. Mr. Druthers remembers his Great Grandfather – who worked at Curio & Co. side by side with his father – bringing out a collection of matchbooks collected from travels around the world. “Listening to his stories of those matchbooks; well I was right there with him…in places I’d never even seen.”

All of us at Curio & Co. are honored to help you build your collection of memories – to rediscover your own childhood treasures and share in some of our favorite memories of places you might not have seen yet.
name: Curio & Co.
